# 10 — Performance

## Hard Targets (non-negotiable)
- **Lighthouse ≥ 95** (Performance, mobile).
- **LCP < 2.5s** — LCP element is hero TEXT, not 3D, not video.
- **INP < 200ms** — keep the main thread free; defer/break up heavy JS.
- **CLS < 0.1** — reserve space for hero, 3D canvas, images, video, sticky bars.
- **60fps** animations (see 06-motion).

## Loading Strategy
- **Critical path = hero text + CTA + countdown.** These render fast and standalone.
- **Lazy-load the 3D AI Core** (`next/dynamic`, `ssr:false`), gated by viewport + device tier. Never in the initial bundle.
- Lazy-load below-the-fold sections, testimonial video (poster first, load on interaction/visibility), and any heavy lib.
- Code-split GSAP/Lenis/3D so the hero TTI isn't penalized by motion/3D weight.

## Asset Discipline
- **Fonts:** self-host Space Grotesk + Inter via `next/font`; subset; preload only used weights; `font-display: swap` or size-adjust to kill CLS/FOIT.
- **Images:** `next/image`, AVIF/WebP, correct sizes, lazy by default, explicit width/height. No stock photos (see brand). Instructor/testimonial assets compressed and graded.
- **Video:** never autoplay heavy video; poster image + click/visibility to load; prefer streamed/hosted, not bundled.
- **Icons:** tree-shaken individual imports, not whole icon packs.

## JavaScript Budget
- Initial client JS kept lean; the 3D chunk is separate and on-demand.
- Prefer Server Components; ship interactivity only where needed.
- No unnecessary client libraries; audit every dependency for size before adding.

## 3D Performance (cross-ref 05-3d)
- dpr cap `[1,2]`, device-tiered particle counts, pause loop offscreen/on blur, reduce on low-end and reduced-motion.
- WebGPU-first with WebGL2 fallback and a static poster no-WebGL fallback.

## Rendering & Caching
- Static/ISR for the page shell; edge-cache static assets with long max-age + immutable hashing.
- Stream server components; avoid blocking data fetches on the critical render.

## Measurement & Guardrails
- Wire `web-vitals` reporting (LCP/INP/CLS/TTFB) to analytics.
- Treat a Lighthouse regression below 95, or any vital breaching budget, as a build blocker.
- Test on mid-tier mobile + throttled network, not just desktop.

## Performance Don'ts
No render-blocking third-party scripts, no layout-shifting late content, no unoptimized images, no eager 3D, no giant client bundles, no animating layout properties.
